ll":{"docCount":1,"idf":2.252762968495368},"arity":{"docCount":1,"idf":2.252762968495368},"indicate":{"docCount":1,"idf":2.252762968495368},"wrong":{"docCount":1,"idf":2.252762968495368},"number":{"docCount":1,"idf":2.252762968495368}},"documents":{"ep_ci_failure_001":{"taskId":"-Engine-Tester/actions/runs/24250536747))","episodeId":"ep_ci_failure_001","source":"ci_failure","content":"Task: -Engine-Tester/actions/runs/24250536747)) | Outcome: failed | Observation: The pipeline completed all stages except ship, which failed on git push due to stale remote state — another process updated main while this pipeline was running. The verify stage completed after 1 retry but produced typecheck errors in the report, suggesting the retry may have passed without properly resolving the underlying TypeScript type mismatches in PagesPageConfig validation. | Failed at: ship | Suggestion: Add a `git fetch origin main` step before the ship stage's force-push to ensure the local ref is up-to-date with remote, and investigate whether the verify stage's retry logic is properly re-running type checks rather than passing cached results. | Flaw: ship — Git push rejected due to stale remote ref — no fetch/update before push | Stages: taskify:completed, plan:completed, build:completed, verify:completed, review:completed, review-fix:completed, ship:failed","createdAt":"2026-04-10T16:17:53.227Z","wordCount":963,"positions":[0,7,14,21,29,34,50,59,68,85,94,108,115,122,134,144,148,153,160,166,173,181,189,197,205,210,221,234,247,254,260,270,278,288,297,307,321,329,344,359,366,374,383,397,408,419,424,438,454,468,479,486,498,505,509,515,522,528,533,544,549,557,563,571,582,588,595,601,611,623,635,647,654,662,668,677,686,689,697,702,709,716,721,729,736,747,753,760,764,769,778,785,791,798,804,807,813,820,827,834,842,850,861,866,877,883,894,901,912,919,930,937,941,952,957]},"ep_stage_diary_001":{"taskId":"decompose-2779-260418-164551","episodeId":"ep_stage_diary_001","source":"stage_diary","content":"{\"stage\":\"review\",\"insights\":[{\"kind\":\"gotcha\",\"text\":\"Creating services per request (e.g. `createNotificationService()` in route handlers) resets in-memory state and causes data loss across requests.\",\"scope\":\"src/services\"},{\"kind\":\"lesson\",\"text\":\"A singleton store module-level (`let store = ...`) is initialized once at load time; if that store is later replaced by reassignment inside a factory function, callers still hold the old reference and\",\"scope\":\"src/services\"},{\"kind\":\"convention\",\"text\":\"Prefer singleton class instances (shared `static` field) over module-level `let` variables for shared mutable state — the class field is stable and won't be shadowed.\",\"scope\":\"src/services\"}]}","createdAt":"2026-04-18T17:15:57.997Z","wordCount":699,"positions":[2,10,19,32,39,48,55,64,73,77,92,124,130,140,150,157,167,174,179,184,191,203,211,215,228,235,244,253,263,269,276,284,288,305,317,325,330,344,353,359,371,384,393,401,411,419,425,434,438,454,462,466,479,486,499,506,513,523,529,540,548,556,563,568,575,582,587,601,608,616,628,634,643,654,663,675,683,687]},"ep_stage_diary_002":{"taskId":"decompose-2779-260418-164551","episodeId":"ep_stage_diary_002","source":"stage_diary","content":"{\"stage\":\"review-fix\",\"insights\":[{\"kind\":\"gotcha\",\"text\":\"Calling createNotificationService() at request time creates a fresh in-memory store per request — data written in one handler is invisible to another.\",\"scope\":\"src/services/notificationService.ts:64-66\"},{\"kind\":\"lesson\",\"text\":\"Use a singleton service instance (top-level `let service`) initialized once, not a factory called per request, when the store is in-memory.\",\"scope\":\"src/services/notificationService.ts\"},{\"kind\":\"convention\",\"text\":\"TDD ordering: write tests first per area, then implementation, per step in the plan.\",\"scope\":\"plan.md step ordering\"}]}","createdAt":"2026-04-18T17:30:37.709Z","wordCount":626,"positions":[2,10,17,23,36,43,52,59,67,98,106,111,121,130,137,143,147,157,162,173,177,188,201,212,220,224,233,253,256,259,266,273,282,289,295,305,313,323,327,334,338,348,360,366,372,380,387,391,409,421,431,439,443,452,472,479,486,499,506,510,520,526,532,538,542,553,569,573,585,593,601,606,609,614]},"ep_stage_diary_003":{"taskId":"decompose-2779-260418-164551","episodeId":"ep_stage_diary_003","source":"stage_diary","content":"{\"stage\":\"review\",\"insights\":[{\"kind\":\"gotcha\",\"text\":\"A review-fix run introduced new TS errors in test files that weren't in the original build failures. Fixing one thing can break another.\",\"scope\":\"src/routes/notifications.test.ts\"},{\"kind\":\"gotcha\",\"text\":\"A 'uses default store' test pollutes a singleton store, affecting subsequent tests. Tests sharing singleton state must clean up or isolate.\",\"scope\":\"notificationService.test.ts\"},{\"kind\":\"lesson\",\"text\":\"When mocking NextRequest via `makeNextRequest` with spread, ensure all constructor arguments are accounted for or TS2554 errors occur.\",\"scope\":\"test mocking\"}]}","createdAt":"2026-04-18T17:32:11.616Z","wordCount":628,"positions":[2,10,19,32,39,48,57,64,68,72,83,87,90,100,105,116,131,140,146,156,163,167,177,183,194,202,206,213,227,232,239,246,255,265,270,278,285,290,301,311,318,328,339,346,352,360,370,376,381,387,393,404,412,432,437,444,451,460,472,480,492,497,519,527,538,550,564,581,588,595,604,612,617]},"ep_stage_diary_004":{"taskId":"decompose-2779-260418-164551","episodeId":"ep_stage_diary_004","source":"stage_diary","content":"{\"stage\":\"review-fix\",\"insights\":[{\"kind\":\"gotcha\",\"text\":\"Review-fix runs that touch test files can introduce new TypeScript compilation errors even while fixing runtime issues — always run build after fixing tests.\",\"scope\":\"src/routes/notifications.test.ts\"},{\"kind\":\"lesson\",\"text\":\"Tests for singleton-based services (e.g. default store) that mutate global state must run last or be isolated with beforeEach/teardown to avoid polluting subsequent tests in the same file.\",\"scope\":\"src/services/notificationService.test.ts\"},{\"kind\":\"gotcha\",\"text\":\"Patching a stub back to a real implementation at the end of a test without proper teardown causes singleton pollution that silently breaks unrelated tests in the same suite.\",\"scope\":\"src/services/notificationService.test.ts\"},{\"kind\":\"decision\",\"text\":\"Request-time service instantiation (vs. module-level) was the correct fix for the original bug — it allows request-scoped overrides and prevents shared mutable state across concurrent requests","createdAt":"2026-04-18T17:36:45.082Z","wordCount":1000,"positions":[2,10,17,23,36,43,52,59,66,70,80,86,91,101,111,115,126,138,145,150,156,163,171,180,187,191,197,203,210,219,227,231,238,252,257,264,271,280,287,297,307,313,328,336,348,355,362,368,373,377,388,402,413,425,431,441,452,465,470,478,486,490,499,519,524,531,538,547,554,565,570,580,585,607,616,621,629,636,645,652,662,677,686,693,703,716,721,730,738,742,751,771,776,783,790,801,808,816,821,829,844,848,855,870,878,890,899,908,915,923,930,944,953,960,968,974,981,992]},"ep_stage_diary_005":{"taskId":"decompose-2779-260418-164551","episodeId":"ep_stage_diary_005","source":"stage_diary","content":"{\"stage\":\"review\",\"insights\":[{\"kind\":\"gotcha\",\"text\":\"ServiceResult union type members don't expose .val/.err properties; tests that access these must narrow the type first with guards or casts.\",\"scope\":\"src/services\"},{\"kind\":\"lesson\",\"text\":\"Co-located test files are typechecked as part of the project; test code must satisfy the same TypeScript constraints as production code.\",\"scope\":\"testing\"},{\"kind\":\"lesson\",\"text\":\"Handler call arity mismatches in route test files indicate the test is passing wrong number of arguments to the handler function.\",\"scope\":\"src/routes\"}]}","createdAt":"2026-04-18T17:40:25.769Z","wordCount":582,"positions":[2,10,19,32,39,48,55,69,75,80,88,94,102,107,111,123,134,147,152,163,168,179,189,198,206,210,223,230,239,246,249,257,262,272,287,299,308,313,318,323,335,340,351,366,377,385,393,405,412,421,428,436,441,447,461,467,472,478,491,499,507,513,523,540,548,560,568,572]}},"totalDocs":6}